      "date": "2014-12-13 17:09:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nKit, you are right - the code under the top-level \"if\" condition is identical except for the one error message. It would be better to put it in a small helper function, maybe mdt_pack_acl2body(info, repbody, o) to match mdt_pack_attr2body()?  Please avoid the deep nested \"if\" blocks and just have it return early when possible. The function should also be under CONFIG_FS_POSIX_ACL is this code is so it doesn't generate a warning if that is not set. \n\nThat would reduce code duplication and would avoid similar problems in the future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
